{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_22","type":"command_execution","command":"\"C:\\\\Windows\\\\System32\\\\WindowsPowerShell\\\\v1.0\\\\powershell.exe\" -Command '$path='\"'C:\\\\Users\\\\GJM258\\\\.codex\\\\plugins\\\\cache\\\\game-design-skill\\\\game-design-skill\\\\0.1.0\\\\skills\\\\game-design-skill\\\\references\\\\upstream-workflow-balance-check.md'; \"'$lines=Get-Content $path; for($n=39;$n -le 101;$n++){ '\"'{0,4}: {1}' -f \"'$n, $lines[$n-1] }'","aggregated_output":"  39: ## Phase 4: Perform Analysis\r\n  40: \r\n  41: Run domain-specific checks:\r\n  42: \r\n  43: **Combat balance:**\r\n  44: - Calculate DPS for all weapons/abilities at each power tier\r\n  45: - Check time-to-kill at each tier\r\n  46: - Identify any options that dominate all others (strictly better)\r\n  47: - Check if defensive options can create unkillable states\r\n  48: - Verify damage type/resistance interactions are balanced\r\n  49: \r\n  50: **Economy balance:**\r\n  51: - Map all resource faucets and sinks with flow rates\r\n  52: - Project resource accumulation over time\r\n  53: - Check for infinite resource loops\r\n  54: - Verify gold sinks scale with gold generation\r\n  55: - Check if any items are never worth purchasing\r\n  56: \r\n  57: **Progression balance:**\r\n  58: - Plot the XP curve and power curve\r\n  59: - Check for dead zones (no meaningful progression for too long)\r\n  60: - Check for power spikes (sudden jumps in capability)\r\n  61: - Verify content gates align with expected player power\r\n  62: - Check if skip/grind strategies break intended pacing\r\n  63: \r\n  64: **Loot balance:**\r\n  65: - Calculate expected time to acquire each rarity tier\r\n  66: - Check pity timer math\r\n  67: - Verify no loot is strictly useless at any stage\r\n  68: - Check inventory pressure vs acquisition rate\r\n  69: \r\n  70: ---\r\n  71: \r\n  72: ## Phase 5: Output the Analysis\r\n  73: \r\n  74: ```\r\n  75: ## Balance Check: [System Name]\r\n  76: \r\n  77: ### Data Sources Analyzed\r\n  78: - [List of files read]\r\n  79: \r\n  80: ### Health Summary: [HEALTHY / CONCERNS / CRITICAL ISSUES]\r\n  81: \r\n  82: ### Outliers Detected\r\n  83: | Item/Value | Expected Range | Actual | Issue |\r\n  84: |-----------|---------------|--------|-------|\r\n  85: \r\n  86: ### Degenerate Strategies Found\r\n  87: - [Strategy description and why it is problematic]\r\n  88: \r\n  89: ### Progression Analysis\r\n  90: [Graph description or table showing progression curve health]\r\n  91: \r\n  92: ### Recommendations\r\n  93: | Priority | Issue | Suggested Fix | Impact |\r\n  94: |----------|-------|--------------|--------|\r\n  95: \r\n  96: ### Values That Need Attention\r\n  97: [Specific values with suggested adjustments and rationale]\r\n  98: ```\r\n  99: \r\n 100: ---\r\n 101: \r\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_21","type":"command_execution","command":"\"C:\\\\Windows\\\\System32\\\\WindowsPowerShell\\\\v1.0\\\\powershell.exe\" -Command '$path='\"'C:\\\\Users\\\\GJM258\\\\.codex\\\\plugins\\\\cache\\\\game-design-skill\\\\game-design-skill\\\\0.1.0\\\\skills\\\\game-design-skill\\\\references\\\\upstream-workflow-consistency-check.md'; \"'$lines=Get-Content $path; for($n=85;$n -le 211;$n++){ '\"'{0,4}: {1}' -f \"'$n, $lines[$n-1] }'","aggregated_output":"  85: ## Phase 3: Grep-First Conflict Scan\r\n  86: \r\n  87: For each registered entry, grep every in-scope GDD for the entry's name.\r\n  88: Do NOT do full reads 鈥?extract only the matching lines and their immediate\r\n  89: context (-C 3 lines).\r\n  90: \r\n  91: This is the core optimization: instead of reading 10 GDDs 脳 400 lines each\r\n  92: (4,000 lines), you grep 50 entity names 脳 10 GDDs (50 targeted searches,\r\n  93: each returning ~10 lines on a hit).\r\n  94: \r\n  95: ### 3a: Entity Scan\r\n  96: \r\n  97: For each entity in entity_map:\r\n  98: \r\n  99: ```\r\n 100: Grep pattern=\"[entity_name]\" glob=\"design/gdd/*.md\" output_mode=\"content\" -C 3\r\n 101: ```\r\n 102: \r\n 103: For each GDD hit, extract the values mentioned near the entity name:\r\n 104: - any numeric attributes (counts, costs, durations, ranges, rates)\r\n 105: - any categorical attributes (types, tiers, categories)\r\n 106: - any derived values (totals, outputs, results)\r\n 107: - any other attributes registered in entity_map\r\n 108: \r\n 109: Compare extracted values against the registry entry.\r\n 110: \r\n 111: **Conflict detection:**\r\n 112: - Registry says `[entity_name].[attribute] = [value_A]`. GDD says `[entity_name] has [value_B]`. 鈫?**CONFLICT**\r\n 113: - Registry says `[item_name].[attribute] = [value_A]`. GDD says `[item_name] is [value_B]`. 鈫?**CONFLICT**\r\n 114: - GDD mentions `[entity_name]` but doesn't specify the attribute. 鈫?**NOTE** (no conflict, just unverifiable)\r\n 115: \r\n 116: ### 3b: Item Scan\r\n 117: \r\n 118: For each item in item_map, grep all GDDs for the item name. Extract:\r\n 119: - sell price / value / gold value\r\n 120: - weight\r\n 121: - stack rules (stackable / non-stackable)\r\n 122: - category\r\n 123: \r\n 124: Compare against registry entry values.\r\n 125: \r\n 126: ### 3c: Formula Scan\r\n 127: \r\n 128: For each formula in formula_map, grep all GDDs for the formula name. Extract:\r\n 129: - variable names mentioned near the formula\r\n 130: - output range or cap values mentioned\r\n 131: \r\n 132: Compare against registry entry:\r\n 133: - Different variable names 鈫?**CONFLICT**\r\n 134: - Output range stated differently 鈫?**CONFLICT**\r\n 135: \r\n 136: ### 3d: Constant Scan\r\n 137: \r\n 138: For each constant in constant_map, grep all GDDs for the constant name. Extract:\r\n 139: - Any numeric value mentioned near the constant name\r\n 140: \r\n 141: Compare against registry value:\r\n 142: - Different number 鈫?**CONFLICT**\r\n 143: \r\n 144: ---\r\n 145: \r\n 146: ## Phase 4: Deep Investigation (Conflicts Only)\r\n 147: \r\n 148: For each conflict found in Phase 3, do a targeted full-section read of the\r\n 149: conflicting GDD to get precise context:\r\n 150: \r\n 151: ```\r\n 152: Read path=\"design/gdd/[conflicting_gdd].md\"\r\n 153: ```\r\n 154: (Or use Grep with wider context if the file is large)\r\n 155: \r\n 156: Confirm the conflict with full context. Determine:\r\n 157: 1. **Which GDD is correct?** Check the `source:` field in the registry 鈥?the\r\n 158:    source GDD is the authoritative owner. Any other GDD that contradicts it\r\n 159:    is the one that needs updating.\r\n 160: 2. **Is the registry itself out of date?** If the source GDD was updated after\r\n 161:    the registry entry was written (check git log), the registry may be stale.\r\n 162: 3. **Is this a genuine design change?** If the conflict represents an intentional\r\n 163:    design decision, the resolution is: update the source GDD, update the registry,\r\n 164:    then fix all other GDDs.\r\n 165: \r\n 166: For each conflict, classify:\r\n 167: - **馃敶 CONFLICT** 鈥?same named entity/item/formula/constant with different values\r\n 168:   in different GDDs. Must resolve before architecture begins.\r\n 169: - **鈿狅笍 STALE REGISTRY** 鈥?source GDD value changed but registry not updated.\r\n 170:   Registry needs updating; other GDDs may be correct already.\r\n 171: - **鈩癸笍 UNVERIFIABLE** 鈥?entity mentioned but no comparable attribute stated.\r\n 172:   Not a conflict; just noting the reference.\r\n 173: \r\n 174: ---\r\n 175: \r\n 176: ## Phase 5: Output Report\r\n 177: \r\n 178: ```\r\n 179: ## Consistency Check Report\r\n 180: Date: [date]\r\n 181: Registry entries checked: [N entities, N items, N formulas, N constants]\r\n 182: GDDs scanned: [N] ([list names])\r\n 183: \r\n 184: ---\r\n 185: \r\n 186: ### Conflicts Found (must resolve before architecture)\r\n 187: \r\n 188: 馃敶 [Entity/Item/Formula/Constant Name]\r\n 189:    Registry (source: [gdd]): [attribute] = [value]\r\n 190:    Conflict in [other_gdd].md: [attribute] = [different_value]\r\n 191:    鈫?Resolution needed: [which doc to change and to what]\r\n 192: \r\n 193: ---\r\n 194: \r\n 195: ### Stale Registry Entries (registry behind the GDD)\r\n 196: \r\n 197: 鈿狅笍 [Entry Name]\r\n 198:    Registry says: [value] (written [date])\r\n 199:    Source GDD now says: [new value]\r\n 200:    鈫?Update registry entry to match source GDD, then check referenced_by docs.\r\n 201: \r\n 202: ---\r\n 203: \r\n 204: ### Unverifiable References (no conflict, informational)\r\n 205: \r\n 206: 鈩癸笍 [gdd].md mentions [entity_name] but states no comparable attributes.\r\n 207:    No conflict detected. No action required.\r\n 208: \r\n 209: ---\r\n 210: \r\n 211: ### Clean Entries (no issues found)\r\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_23","type":"agent_message","text":"These two fixtures currently fail as a single cross-system contract. The shared gold rules disagree on value, owner, recipient, and test outcome, so there is no non-guessy authoritative behavior to implement from the pair alone.\n\n**Blockers**\n- The shared gold knobs are defined twice with different values and different owners. Combat sets `kill_gold_reward = 20` and `death_gold_loss_percent = 25` as Combat-owned, while Economy sets the same knobs to `10` and `50` as Economy-owned. That is both a rule contradiction and duplicated tuning-knob ownership, and the pair does not establish which document is authoritative ([combat.md:13](/C:/Users/GJM258/JtheWLToolBox/game-design-skill/verification/fixtures/gdds/combat.md:13), [combat.md:32](/C:/Users/GJM258/JtheWLToolBox/game-design-skill/verification/fixtures/gdds/combat.md:32), [economy.md:13](/C:/Users/GJM258/JtheWLToolBox/game-design-skill/verification/fixtures/gdds/economy.md:13), [economy.md:31](/C:/Users/GJM258/JtheWLToolBox/game-design-skill/verification/fixtures/gdds/economy.md:31)).\n- Combat is internally inconsistent on death-loss ownership. Its Dependencies say it reads an Economy-owned percentage, but its Tuning Knobs say Combat owns that same percentage; Economy also claims ownership. There is no single source of truth for the same event ([combat.md:28](/C:/Users/GJM258/JtheWLToolBox/game-design-skill/verification/fixtures/gdds/combat.md:28), [combat.md:33](/C:/Users/GJM258/JtheWLToolBox/game-design-skill/verification/fixtures/gdds/combat.md:33), [economy.md:27](/C:/Users/GJM258/JtheWLToolBox/game-design-skill/verification/fixtures/gdds/economy.md:27), [economy.md:32](/C:/Users/GJM258/JtheWLToolBox/game-design-skill/verification/fixtures/gdds/economy.md:32)).\n- The kill-reward acceptance criteria cannot both pass. Combat resolves `20` gold to Economy; Economy resolves `10` gold to the player. The conflict is on both amount and recipient, not just wording ([combat.md:38](/C:/Users/GJM258/JtheWLToolBox/game-design-skill/verification/fixtures/gdds/combat.md:38), [economy.md:37](/C:/Users/GJM258/JtheWLToolBox/game-design-skill/verification/fixtures/gdds/economy.md:37)).\n- The death-loss rules are missing the precision/rounding operation needed for deterministic implementation and testing. `25%` and `exactly 50%` are ambiguous on odd balances if gold is integral; if fractional gold is allowed, that precision is unstated. Economy also adds “no cap” while Combat does not address cap behavior ([combat.md:14](/C:/Users/GJM258/JtheWLToolBox/game-design-skill/verification/fixtures/gdds/combat.md:14), [economy.md:14](/C:/Users/GJM258/JtheWLToolBox/game-design-skill/verification/fixtures/gdds/economy.md:14), [economy.md:36](/C:/Users/GJM258/JtheWLToolBox/game-design-skill/verification/fixtures/gdds/economy.md:36)).\n\n**Concerns**\n- Combat’s survivability rule is not tied to a complete incoming-damage formula. Plausible readings include pre-damage capping, post-damage floor-to-1, or resistance-first then floor; those produce different outcomes once Economy’s permanent damage-resistance upgrade is applied, and the docs do not say which interpretation is intended ([combat.md:15](/C:/Users/GJM258/JtheWLToolBox/game-design-skill/verification/fixtures/gdds/combat.md:15), [combat.md:19](/C:/Users/GJM258/JtheWLToolBox/game-design-skill/verification/fixtures/gdds/combat.md:19), [combat.md:37](/C:/Users/GJM258/JtheWLToolBox/game-design-skill/verification/fixtures/gdds/combat.md:37), [economy.md:15](/C:/Users/GJM258/JtheWLToolBox/game-design-skill/verification/fixtures/gdds/economy.md:15)).\n- The reward contradiction changes economy pacing by 2x. `upgrade_cost = 50 * 2^tier` yields `12,800` gold for tier 8 and `25,550` gold across tiers `0-8`, so switching between `10` and `20` gold per kill halves or doubles the required reward events before consumable spend or death loss. That is a proven range swing, but there is no encounter-count, expedition-length, success-rate, or spend-rate evidence to tell whether either pace is intended ([economy.md:19](/C:/Users/GJM258/JtheWLToolBox/game-design-skill/verification/fixtures/gdds/economy.md:19), [economy.md:22](/C:/Users/GJM258/JtheWLToolBox/game-design-skill/verification/fixtures/gdds/economy.md:22), [combat.md:13](/C:/Users/GJM258/JtheWLToolBox/game-design-skill/verification/fixtures/gdds/combat.md:13), [economy.md:13](/C:/Users/GJM258/JtheWLToolBox/game-design-skill/verification/fixtures/gdds/economy.md:13)).\n- No direct player-fantasy contradiction appears between the two local Fantasy sections; both point toward preparation. The issue is missing pillar evidence and an underspecified bridge: without a shared pillars/anti-pillars source, and without a combat-side explanation of how resistance supports readable counterplay, pillar alignment and fantasy coherence are only partially verifiable ([combat.md:9](/C:/Users/GJM258/JtheWLToolBox/game-design-skill/verification/fixtures/gdds/combat.md:9), [economy.md:9](/C:/Users/GJM258/JtheWLToolBox/game-design-skill/verification/fixtures/gdds/economy.md:9), [economy.md:15](/C:/Users/GJM258/JtheWLToolBox/game-design-skill/verification/fixtures/gdds/economy.md:15)).\n- The source/sink evidence is incomplete. The pair names kill rewards, death loss, consumables, and upgrades, but only upgrade costs are quantified, so sink-over-source pressure and no-catch-up risk are structural concerns rather than proven balance failures from the available evidence ([combat.md:13](/C:/Users/GJM258/JtheWLToolBox/game-design-skill/verification/fixtures/gdds/combat.md:13), [combat.md:14](/C:/Users/GJM258/JtheWLToolBox/game-design-skill/verification/fixtures/gdds/combat.md:14), [economy.md:5](/C:/Users/GJM258/JtheWLToolBox/game-design-skill/verification/fixtures/gdds/economy.md:5), [economy.md:14](/C:/Users/GJM258/JtheWLToolBox/game-design-skill/verification/fixtures/gdds/economy.md:14), [economy.md:19](/C:/Users/GJM258/JtheWLToolBox/game-design-skill/verification/fixtures/gdds/economy.md:19)).\n\n**Optional Improvements**\n- Add one shared cross-system contract for reward routing, death-loss application, and gold precision/rounding so both docs reference one behavior instead of restating values.\n- Add one scenario-level acceptance test for `kill echo -> gain gold -> die -> buy resistance upgrade` to lock activation order, data flow, and player-facing outcome at the combat/economy boundary.\n- Add minimal evidence tables for expected kills per expedition, target deaths per run, consumable price bands, resistance effect expression, and intended upgrade-purchase cadence.\n\n**Sources Applied**\n- `SKILL.md`\n- `references/provenance.md`\n- `references/upstream-workflow-review-all-gdds.md`\n- `references/upstream-workflow-consistency-check.md`\n- `references/upstream-workflow-balance-check.md`"}}
{"type":"turn.completed","usage":{"input_tokens":203711,"cached_input_tokens":162432,"output_tokens":13196,"reasoning_output_tokens":9375}}
